cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with multimodal representation learning for visual question answering and visual relationship detection, which are tasks related to computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, the paper also introduces a new fusion model that leverages the notion of block-term ranks, which is a concept related to tensor decomposition and can be considered as a machine learning technique. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
